'''Yvette Kosmann-Schwarzbach''' (born 30 April 1941)<ref>[http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n93108267.html (Yvette Kosmann-Schwarzbach) data sh. (b. 4-30-41)]</ref><ref>[http://catalogue.bnf.fr/servlet/RechercheEquation;jsessionid=85C81B2CD802E8FCDCFD5835BE883707?TexteCollection=HGARSTUVWXYZ1DIECBMJNQLOKP&TexteTypeDoc=DESNFPIBTMCJOV&Equation=IDP%3Dcb12436908f&host=catalogue Naissance :  1941-04-30]</ref> is a French [[mathematician]] and [[professor]]. She has been teaching [[mathematics]] at the [[Lille University of Science and Technology]] and at the [[École polytechnique]] since 1993. Kosmann-Schwarzbach obtained her [[doctoral degree]] in 1970 at the [[University of Paris]] under supervision of [[André Lichnerowicz]] on a dissertation titled ''Dérivées de Lie des spineurs'' ([[Lie derivative]]s of spinors).<ref>[http://catalogue.bnf.fr/servlet/RechercheEquation;jsessionid=85C81B2CD802E8FCDCFD5835BE883707?TexteCollection=HGARSTUVWXYZ1DIECBMJNQLOKP&TexteTypeDoc=DESNFPIBTMCJOV&Equation=IDP%3Dcb12436908f&host=catalogue Docteur en mathématiques (Paris, 1970). - En poste au Centre de mathématiques, École polytechnique, Palaiseau, France (en 1993)]</ref><ref>Kosmann-Schwarzbach: ''[http://www.ams.org/notices/200902/rtx090200244p.pdf Tribute to Andre Lichnerowicz (1915-1988)]. [[Notices of the American Mathematical Society]]'', Vol. 56, No. 2. Accessed 30 April 2014.</ref><ref name="autogenerated317">Kosmann Y. (1972), ''[https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2FBF02428822 Dérivées de Lie des spineurs]'', ''[[Annali di Matematica Pura ed Applicata]]'',  '''91''' (1) pp. 317–395</ref> She is the author of over fifty articles on [[differential geometry]], [[algebra]] and [[mathematical physics]], as well as the co-editor of several books concerning the theory of [[integrable systems]]. The [[Kosmann lift]] in differential geometry is named after her.<ref>Fatibene L., Ferraris M., [[Mauro Francaviglia|Francaviglia M.]] and Godina M. (1996), ''A geometric definition of Lie derivative for Spinor Fields'', in: ''Proceedings of the 6th International Conference on Differential Geometry and Applications,'' August 28th–September 1st 1995 (Brno, Czech Republic), Janyska J., Kolář I. & J. Slovák J.
(Eds.), Masaryk University, Brno, pp. 549–558</ref><ref>Godina M. and Matteucci P. (2003), ''Reductive G-structures and Lie derivatives'', ''[[Journal of Geometry and Physics]]'', '''47''', pp. 66–86</ref>

== Works ==
* ''Groups and Symmetries: From Finite Groups to Lie Groups.'' Springer 2010, {{isbn|978-0387788654}}.
* ''The Noether Theorems: Invariance and Conservation Laws in the Twentieth Century: Invariance and Conservation Laws in the 20th Century.'' Translated by Bertram Schwarzbach. Springer 2011, {{isbn|978-0387878676}}.

